{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"shapely-sickening-skipper","creation_channel":"python","description":"## Context\nCodex sessions can invoke ambient Ruff and miss mypy even though GitHub CI and Claude Code use the repository environment. Align persistent Codex guidance with the documented local development setup so quality gates reproduce CI.\n\n## Plan\n- Inspect Claude Code hooks/configuration, Make targets, and local-development documentation to identify the authoritative environment bootstrap.\n- Add concise Codex-facing AGENTS.md guidance that selects the repository virtual environment before running rebar, make lint, make typecheck, or other development gates.\n- Provision the current isolated worktree using the documented workflow and verify both gates without changing their implementation or formatting unrelated files.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] AGENTS.md tells Codex sessions how to bootstrap and activate the repository environment using the same documented workflow as Claude Code.\n- [ ] The guidance prevents ambient Ruff or missing mypy from being mistaken for repository failures.\n- [ ] make lint exits zero in the correctly configured worktree.\n- [ ] make typecheck exits zero in the correctly configured worktree.\n- [ ] The change cites the authoritative project setup documentation and remains concise.\n","id":"99c7-3f0e-3685-484f","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Document Codex repository environment setup"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784655454146882001,"uuid":"c9a5fc58-89d4-4ff2-a2a9-064a19bbd18a"}